{
  "luaScript": {
    "id": "luaScript",
    "title":"Avoid dynamic Lua script",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "luaScript-1",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "Refrain from generating dynamic scripts, which can cause your Lua cache to grow and get out of control. Memory is consumed as scripts are loaded. If you have to use dynamic Lua scripts, then remember to track your Lua memory consumption and flush the cache periodically with a "
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-2",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/commands/script-flush/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=luaScript/",
          "name": "SCRIPT FLUSH"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": ". Also do not hardcode and/or programmatically generate key names in your Lua scripts because they do not work in a clustered Redis setup."
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-4",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-5",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "See the "
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-6",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/manual/programmability/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=luaScript/",
          "name": "documentation"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "luaScript-7",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " to learn more about programmability in Redis."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["code_changes"]
  },
  "useSmallerKeys": {
    "id": "useSmallerKeys",
    "title":"Use smaller keys",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "useSmallerKeys-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Shorten key names to optimize memory usage. Though, in general, descriptive key names are always preferred, these large key names can eat a lot of the memory."
      },
      {
        "id": "useSmallerKeys-2",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "useSmallerKeys-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "See the "
      },
      {
        "id": "useSmallerKeys-4",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/management/optimization/memory-optimization/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=useSmallerKeys/",
          "name": "documentation"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "useSmallerKeys-5",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " for more memory optimization strategies."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["code_changes"]
  },
  "bigHashes": {
    "id": "bigHashes",
    "telemetryEvent": "shardHashes",
    "title": "Shard big hashes to small hashes",
    "redisStack": true,
    "tutorial": "/quick-guides/document/working-with-hashes.md",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "bigHashes-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "If you have a hash with a large number of field-value pairs (> 5,000), and each pair is small enough - break it into smaller hashes to optimize memory usage. Additionally, try using smaller or shortened field names."
      },
      {
        "id": "bigHashes-2",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "bigHashes-3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Try the interactive tutorial to learn how to work with index and query documents modeled with hashes."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["code_changes", "configuration_changes"]
  },
  "avoidLogicalDatabases": {
    "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases",
    "title": "Avoid using logical databases",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Using logical databases is an anti-pattern that Salvatore Sanfilippo, the creator of Redis, once called the worst design mistake he ever made in Redis."
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-2",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-3",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Although supported in Redis, logical databases are neither independent nor isolated in any other way and can freeze each other. Also, they are not supported by any clustering system (open source or Redis Enterprise clustering)."
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-4",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-5",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "If you need a multi-tenant environment, try "
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-6",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.com/try-free/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=avoidLogicalDatabases",
          "name": "Redis Cloud"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "avoidLogicalDatabases-7",
        "type": "span",
        "value": ", where each tenant has its own Redis database endpoint which is completely isolated from the other Redis databases."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["code_changes"]
  },
  "combineSmallStringsToHashes": {
    "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes",
    "title": "Combine small strings to hashes",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-1",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "The strings data type has an overhead of about 90 bytes on a 64-bit machine, so if there is no need for different expiration values for these keys, combine small strings into a larger hash to optimize the memory usage. Also, ensure that the hash has less than "
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-2",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-entries"
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " elements and that the size of each element is within "
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-4",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-values"
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-5",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " bytes."
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-6",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-7",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Though this approach should not be used if you need different expiration values for string keys."
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-8",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-9",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "See the "
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-10",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/management/optimization/memory-optimization/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=combineSmallStringsToHashes",
          "name": "documentation"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "combineSmallStringsToHashes-11",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " for more memory optimization strategies."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["code_changes"]
  },
  "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries": {
    "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries",
    "title": "Increase the set-max-intset-entries",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Several set values with IntSet encoding exceed the set-max-intset-entries. Change the configuration in redis.conf to efficiently use the IntSet encoding. Though increasing this value will lead to an increase in the latency of set operations and CPU utilization."
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-2",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "Run "
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-3",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "INFO COMMANDSTATS"
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-4",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " before and after making this change to verify the latency numbers."
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-5",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-6",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "See the "
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-7",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/management/optimization/memory-optimization/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries/",
          "name": "documentation"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "increaseSetMaxIntsetEntries-8",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " for more memory optimization strategies."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["configuration_changes"]
  },
  "hashHashtableToZiplist": {
    "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist",
    "title": "Convert hashtable to ziplist for hashes",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-1",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "Increase "
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-2",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-entries"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " and/or "
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-4",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-values"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-5",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-6",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "If any value for a key exceeds "
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-7",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-entries"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-8",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " or "
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-9",
        "type": "code",
        "value": "hash-max-ziplist-values"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-10",
        "type": "span",
        "value": ", it is stored automatically as a Hashtable instead of a Ziplist, which consumes almost double the memory. So to save the memory, increase the configurations and convert your hashtables to ziplist. The trade-off can be an increase in latency and possibly an increase in CPU utilization."
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-11",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-12",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "See the "
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-13",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/management/optimization/memory-optimization/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=hashHashtableToZiplist/",
          "name": "documentation"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "hashHashtableToZiplist-14",
        "type": "span",
        "value": " for more memory optimization strategies."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["configuration_changes"]
  },
