    "title":"Try using the Redis native time series data structure and querying capabilities",
    "redisStack": true,
    "tutorial": "/redis_stack/redis_for_time_series.md",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "RTS-1",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "If you are using sorted sets to store time series data, consider using the "
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-2",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.com/try-free/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=optimizeTimeSeries/",
          "name": "time series capabilities"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "."
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-4",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-5",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Take advantage of advanced toolings such as downsampling and aggregation to ensure a small memory footprint without impacting performance."
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-6",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-7",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "It also supports a variety of queries for visualization and monitoring with built-in connectors to popular tools."
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-8",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-9",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "The capabilities are part of Redis Stack, Redis Enterprise Cloud, and Redis Enterprise Software."
      },
      {
        "id": "RTS-10",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
