  "searchIndexes": {
    "id": "searchIndexes",
    "title":"Try using the indexing, querying, and full-text search, natively developed in Redis",
    "redisStack": true,
    "tutorial": "/quick-guides/document/introduction.md",
    "content": [
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "If you are using sorted sets for indexing comes with downsides:"
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-2",
        "type": "list",
        "value": [
          [
            {
              "id": "searchIndexes-2.1",
              "type": "span",
              "value": "limited query flexibility such as filtering, sorting, or aggregations;"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "id": "searchIndexes-2.2",
              "type": "span",
              "value": "the risk of outdated or incorrect entries when other applications do not properly update or maintain the index;"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "id": "searchIndexes-2.3",
              "type": "span",
              "value": "difficulty in handling updates and deletions;"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "id": "searchIndexes-2.4",
              "type": "span",
              "value": "lack of horizontal scaling;"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "id": "searchIndexes-2.5",
              "type": "span",
              "value": "increased storage requirements to store both scores and members."
            }
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-3",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "Consider using the "
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-4",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://redis.io/docs/stack/search/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=searchIndexes/",
          "name": "query and search capabilities"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-5",
        "type": "span",
        "value": ", natively developed in Redis, for performing text searches and complex structured queries. It offers real-time searching through synchronous indexing, ensuring read-your-writes consistency, without compromising the database performance."
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-6",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-7",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "The capability is part of Redis Stack, Redis Enterprise Cloud, and Redis Enterprise Software. Also supported in an "
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-8",
        "type": "link",
        "value": {
          "href": "https://docs.redis.com/latest/modules/redisearch/redisearch-active-active/?utm_source=redisinsight&utm_medium=recommendation&utm_campaign=searchIndexes/",
          "name": "Active-Active setup"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-9",
        "type": "span",
        "value": "."
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-10",
        "type": "spacer",
        "value": "l"
      },
      {
        "id": "searchIndexes-11",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "value": "Try the interactive tutorial to learn how to index and query documents modeled with JSON or hashes."
      }
    ],
    "badges": ["upgrade"]
  },
